description: Returns the resolution path of an engagement. For example, the escalation plan engaged in an incident might target an on-call schedule that includes several contacts in a rotation, but just one contact on-call when the incident starts. The resolution path indicates the hierarchy of escalation plan > on-call schedule > contact.

parameters.name: PageId
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact engaged for the incident.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of items to return. Use this token to get the next set of results.

nested_items.name: PageResolutions
nested_items.description: Information about the resolution for an engagement.

nested_items.name: ContactArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a contact in the engagement resolution process.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of contact for a resolution step.

nested_items.name: StageIndex
nested_items.description: The stage in the escalation plan that resolves to this contact.
